<%# locals: (workspaces:, current_workspace:) -%>
<%# Desktop settings-sidebar wrapper — provides the <aside> landmark
    and the boxed sidebar visual chrome (fixed 256px width, surface
    background, right border). For the actual contents (switcher +
    nav items + Pundit gating), see _settings_sidebar_items.html.erb,
    which is also rendered directly into the mobile-accordion
    content_for slot WITHOUT this chrome — that's how mobile sees the
    sidebar contents flow inline instead of as a nested sidebar.

    Workspace switcher: a trigger+dropdown row at the top of the sidebar
    contents (shared/_settings_sidebar_switcher.html.erb) shows the
    current workspace and reveals the full workspace list on click —
    Path Y Phase A, restoring switching to the sidebar in a compact form
    after the always-open inline list (Phase 2) was retired by panel review. -%>
<aside aria-label="<%= t("settings.sidebar.aria_label") %>"
       class="w-64 shrink-0 px-4 py-6 border-r border-border bg-surface">
  <%= render "shared/settings_sidebar_items",
        workspaces: workspaces,
        current_workspace: current_workspace %>
</aside>
